1. Nf3 d5
{ This move was played 32% of the time after 1.Nf3 on lichess.org. To our big surprise, 1... Nf6 is the second most frequent move but only at 16%! So, the chances for an average player to see 1... d5 are double those of 1... Nf6. }
2. b3 Nf6 3. Bb2 c5
{ •  3...e6  4.c4  transposes to @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/5N2/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 1@@EndFEN@@  1...Nf6  2.b3  e6  3.Bb2  d5  4.c4  @@StartBracket@@see the variation@@EndBracket@@.   •  3...Bf5  4.g3  transposes to @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/5N2/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 1@@EndFEN@@  1...d5  2.b3  Bf5  3.Bb2  Nf6  4.g3  @@StartBracket@@see the variation@@EndBracket@@.   •  3...c6  4.g3  Bg4  5.Bg2  Nbd7  6.O-O  e6  7.c4  Bd6  8.d4  transposes to @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/5N2/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 1@@EndFEN@@  1...d5  2.b3  Bg4  3.Bb2  Nd7  4.g3  Ngf6  5.Bg2  e6  6.O-O  Bd6  7.c4  c6  8.d4  @@StartBracket@@see the variation@@EndBracket@@.   •  3...Nc6  4.e3  transposes to @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/5N2/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 1@@EndFEN@@  1...d5  2.b3  Nc6  3.Bb2  Nf6  4.e3  @@StartBracket@@see the variation@@EndBracket@@. }
4. e3 g6
{ •  4...Nc6  5.Bb5  transposes to @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/5N2/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 1@@EndFEN@@  1...d5  2.b3  c5  3.e3  Nc6  4.Bb2  Nf6  5.Bb5  @@StartBracket@@see the variation@@EndBracket@@.   •  4...e6  5.c4  Be7  6.cxd5  exd5  7.Be2  O-O  8.O-O  Nc6  9.d4  Bg4  10.dxc5  Bxc5  11.Nc3  transposes to @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/5N2/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 1@@EndFEN@@  1.Nf3  Nf6  2.b3  e6  3.Bb2  d5  4.c4  Be7  5.e3  O-O  6.Nc3  c5  7.cxd5  exd5  8.d4  Bg4  9.Be2  Nc6  10.dxc5  Bxc5  11.O-O  @@StartBracket@@see the variation@@EndBracket@@.   •  4...Nbd7  Makes as much sense as playing a super theoretical 35-move line against Caruana. Or sticking your fingers in the outlet. You get the point.  5.c4  e6  6.cxd5  exd5  7.d4⩲ }
5. c4 dxc4 { Arguably, a better option than Bg7. } 6. Bxc4 Bg7 7. O-O O-O 8. d4
{ A standard idea we have observed earlier with the bishop on g2. Here, we want to open the files, bring the rooks to d1 and c1, and advance e4. }
8... cxd4 9. Nxd4 Bd7 10. Nd2 Nc6 11. Qe2 { The plan: Rac1, Rfd1, Nf3, e4. } *

