1. Nf3 g6
{ We know quite a few people who play 1... g6 pretty much against anything. In our not-so-humble opinion, 2. e4 will wreck their defenses and inflict severe pain on the Black's king. Chapter 4.1 will cover 2...Bg7, which leads to Pirc/ Modern Defense type of positions, 4.2 and 4.3 will deal with 2... c5, which may lead to a rare line of Pirc or Accelerated Dragon variation of Sicilian Defense.  Arguably, 1... g6 is one of the worst moves out there against 1. Nf3. Black simply gives away too much space in the middle. }
2. e4
{ We must bite the bullet, take a deep breath, and go e4 as soon as on move 2! }
2... c5
{ A popular move, leading either to some rare version of Pirc/Modern Defense or to Sicilian Defense, Accelerated Dragon variation. Such is the nature of chess openings - you never know what you get until a few moves into the game. White has a variety of decent options here. We will take a close look at one of the most promising ones, the early queen development on move 4. }
3. d4 cxd4 4. Qxd4
{ This particular line of Sicilian is so bad for Black that would have been a crime not to attempt to punish it! }
4... Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Qa4 Bg7
{ Allows e5 and thus can't be recommended. This objectively weak move closely trails the most common move on lichess.org 6... d6 - 46.8% vs. 48.2%! So, by playing the line we recommend, you may get a winning position against roughly half of your opponents by simply studying the course material! }
7. e5 Ng8 { 7...Nh5  8.g4+-  Traps the knight and wins the game. } 8. Bf4 f6
{ Otherwise, Black is running out of any reasonable moves.  8...Nh6  9.h3  O-O  10.O-O-O+-  White's position is technically already winning. Even though we are not up in material, our spacial advantage is absolutely overwhelming. }
9. exf6 Nxf6 10. O-O-O
{ We would always castle long if we could. It's so much fun! } 10... O-O 11.
Bc4+ Kh8 12. Rhe1
{ White's pieces look completely symmetrical. One of the ideas might be going Ng5 if Black decides to play d7-d6 or any other move than Qa5. For the purposes of the Quickstarter, the line ends with this move. You can study our full analysis here. }
