2. d4 { Don't let them play e5 for free! Any other moves are vastly inferior. }
2... c6 3. e4 Bg4
{ 3...Nf6  4.Nc3  transposes to @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/5N2/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 1@@EndFEN@@  1...d6  2.d4  Nf6  3.Nc3  c6  4.e4  @@StartBracket@@see the variation@@EndBracket@@. }
4. h3
{ You have probably noticed so far that some moves keep recurring on a regular basis. Playing h3 when the bishop is on g4 is one of those frequent ideas. }
4... Bh5
{ 4...Bxf3  5.Qxf3  e5  6.Bc4  Nf6  7.dxe5  Unlike in other similar lines, we can castle short and then drag the knight to f5. }
5. g4 Bg6 6. Nc3
{ White's position is so good that virtually any plan is fine here. Knowing our predilection to long castles, you probably have guessed that we are going to suggest Qe2, Bf4, O-O-O. }
