3. Nc3 d5 4. Qd3 { Preparing e4. } 4... e6 5. e4 Bb4 6. e5
{ Taking on d5 is quite benign, so pushing the pawn forward and gaining some control in the center is our only viable option. }
6... Ne4 7. Nd2 { Fighting the knight on e4 as soon as we can. } 7... f5 8.
Ncxe4 { f3 wasn't feasible because of Qh4. } 8... fxe4 9. Qg3 O-O 10. Be2
{ The plan: c3, O-O, f3 @@StartBracket@@most likely@@EndBracket@@ or f4. White has a slightly better game due to a better pawn structure and Black's inferior bishop on c8. }
