6... Nh6 7. O-O Bc5 8. h3
{ Making sure the knight never gets to g4 and will be stuck on h6 for a long while. }
8... O-O 9. a4
{ Gaining some ground on the queenside and stopping Black from playing b5. }
9... Qe7 10. a5 Kh8 11. Qh5
{ Provoking Nf6, which won't let Black play f6 and kick out our knight at any point. }
11... Nf6 12. Qe2 { The plan: Nd2, Rd1, Nf1, c3, b4. } *

