1. Nf3
{ We will now consider Dutch-related structures arising after 1... f5. We recommend sticking with 2. b3 - our favorite bishop fianchetto. One major takeaway from this chapter: always aim to break in the center with e4! We especially recommend studying the game after 8. c4 closely. To make these lines more digestible for the learners, we have split them into two parts - chapter 6.1 and chapter 6.2. }
1... f5
{ You know what's crazy? An average player on lichess.org blunders a pawn after 1... e5 three times more often  (!!)  than plays a normal-looking 1... f5! We still encourage you to learn how to handle 1... f5 since it can be played by anybody who likes Dutch Defense. }
2. b3 Nf6
{ •  2...e6  3.Bb2  Nf6  4.g3  transposes to the mainline.   •  2...b6  3.Bb2  Bb7  4.g3  e6  5.Bg2  Nf6  6.O-O  Be7  7.c4  O-O  8.d3  transposes to @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppppp1pp/8/5p2/8/1P3N2/P1PPPPPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 0 2@@EndFEN@@  2...Nf6  3.Bb2  e6  4.g3  Be7  5.Bg2  O-O  6.O-O  b6  7.c4  Bb7  8.d3  @@StartBracket@@see the variation@@EndBracket@@. }
3. Bb2 e6 4. g3 Be7
{ •  4...b6  5.Bg2  Bb7  6.O-O  Be7  7.c4  O-O  8.d3  transposes to  4...Be7  5.Bg2  O-O  6.O-O  b6  7.c4  Bb7  8.d3  @@StartBracket@@see the variation@@EndBracket@@.   •  4...g6  looks odd to combine both ...e6 and ...g6.  5.Bg2  Bg7  6.O-O  O-O  7.c4  This line is a no-brainer. We suggest winning some space with c4, d4, Nc3, Qc2, e4.  7...d6  8.d4  Qe7  9.Nc3⩲   •  4...d6  5.d4  Be7  6.Bg2  O-O  7.O-O  transposes to the mainline. }
5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O d6
{ 6...Qe8  7.c4  Qh5  @@StartBracket@@  7...d6  8.d4  transposes to the mainline.@@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@rnb2rk1/ppppb1pp/4pn2/5p1q/2P5/1P3NP1/PB1PPPBP/RN1Q1RK1 w - - 1 8@@EndFEN@@  8.d4  d6  9.Nc3  transposes to the mainline.   6...Nc6  the knight doesn't belong on c6.  7.c4  d6  8.d4±  The plan: Nc3, d5, Rc1. }
7. d4 Ne4
{ A little premature knight move, looking especially strange considering Black's undeveloped queenisde. }
8. Nbd2 Bf6 9. Ne1
{ Immediately challenging the strong e4-knight. For the purposes of the Quickstarter, the line ends with this move. You can study our full analysis here. }
