{ This move leads to one of the lines we have considered before, but with one huge difference: Black is down a tempo. }
9. d3 Nc6 10. Ne5
{ White got a dream position. Black can't even challenge or trade our bishop on g2. Having a much better pawn structure and control the only open file @@StartBracket@@the b-file@@EndBracket@@ is a nice plus, too. }
