1. Nf3 d5 2. b3 Nf6 3. Bb2 Nbd7 4. c4 e6 5. g3
{ The pawn structure are tricky. We don't mind getting our bishop on g2 even if Black builds the wall with d5, e6, c6. The reason: Black's bishop on c8 will be completely out of play while we still can breakthrough with e4. }
5... Bd6 6. Bg2 O-O 7. O-O c6 8. d4 { The plan: Nc3, Qc2, e4. } *

