[Black "3...b6 4.c4 e6 "]
[Result "*"]

1. Nf3 d5 2. b3 Nf6 3. Bb2 b6
{ leads to unfavorable Queen's Indian pawn structures for Black. } 4. c4 e6
{ We could also play g3 and then take on d5 a bit later. } 5. cxd5 exd5 6. g3
Bb7 7. Bg2 Be7 8. O-O O-O 9. e3
{ A mysterious move at first. We will see the point in just a little bit. }
9... Nbd7 10. Nc3 Re8 11. Rc1
{ The plan: Ne2-f4, Rc2, Qa1, Rfc1! That's why we put the pawn on e3 a couple of moves ago. }
*

