4. Bb2 a6 5. d4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 Nf6 7. Nxc6
{ The pawn structure a2-b3-c4-e3 vs. a6-c6-d5-e7 is typically better for White. }
7... bxc6 8. Nd2 e6 9. Bd3 Be7 10. O-O O-O 11. c4
{ This common pawn structure may occur in various Sicilian Defenses. Black typically suffers due to limited pawn mobility. White's plan includes playing e4 at some point. }
11... a5 12. Qc2 h6 13. Nf3 Ba6 14. e4
{ Now we have a tight grip on Black's center. } 14... Qb6 15. Rfe1 Rfd8 16.
Rac1 Rac8 17. c5
