4. Bb2 e6 5. Bb5 Ne7 6. c4 a6 7. Ba4
{ We only take on c6 if it helps us to go Ne5 after the capture! } 7... Bd7 8.
O-O Nf5 9. cxd5 exd5 10. Bxc6 { Now is the time! } 10... Bxc6 11. Ne5
{ The knight should always go to e5. } 11... Qc7 12. Qf3
{ Taking advantage of the vulnerable knight on f5 and developing the queen. }
12... Nh4 13. Qh5 Ng6 14. Nxc6 Qxc6 15. d4
{ We are about to trade on c5 and enjoy a powerful attack against the isolated pawn on d5. To make things worse, the bishop on f8 has real issues getting out since it may lose the g7 pawn. }
