4. Bb2 Nf6 5. Bb5
{ Pinning the knight and winning a tempo since Black pretty much has to play Bd7 or otherwise face consequences of a damaged pawn structure after Bb5-c6. }
5... Bd7
{ •  5...a6  Wastes a tempo. Black is forcing us to do what want to do anyway.  6.Bxc6+  bxc6  7.Ne5±   •  5...Qc7  Makes even less sense than  5...Qb6  .  6.c4  a6  7.Be5  Qb6  8.Ba4±  The queen moves to c7 and b6 proved to be a waste of time. }
6. O-O e6 7. d4
