[Result "*"]

1. Nf3 d5 2. b3 Nc6 { The knight is ready to support the e5-advance. } 3. Bb2
d4 { A poor pawn structure decision. } 4. e3 dxe3
{ 4...e5  leads to a giant mess for Black after  5.Bb5± } 5. fxe3 a6 6. Qe2
{ Going for the long castle and launching the attack in the center as soon as possible. }
6... Nf6 7. d4 Bf5 8. Nc3 e6 9. O-O-O
{ We have an overwhelming advantage in development and a better pawn structure due to e3 and d4 pawns vs. pawn on e6 @@StartBracket@@bigger center@@EndBracket@@. If Black shows any signs of hestitation, we would hit them hard with e4 and then d5, thus opening up the e-file and exposing the king on e8. }
