{ 5...Bxf3  6.Qxf3  Nf6  7.Bb5⩲  The plan: c4, Bc6, Nc3, O-O, Rac1. Attack on the queenside and hit the weak pawns on the c-file. }
6. Bb5 a6
{ Should Black choose ...Nge7 instead, we can revert back to the familiar plan we have seen in similar lines: Be2, O-O, d4, c4, Nc3, Rc1. }
7. Bxc6+ bxc6 8. g4
{ It's always a good idea to deal with the pieces that pin us as soon as possible. }
8... Bg6 9. Ne5 { The plan: d3, Nd2, Qe2, O-O-O, f4. } *

