Nc3 e6
{ 4...Nc6  5.d4  cxd4  6.Nxd4  e6  7.Bb2  transposes to @@StartFEN@@rn1qkbnr/pb1ppppp/1p6/2p5/4P3/1PN2N2/P1PP1PPP/R1BQKB1R b KQkq - 2 4@@EndFEN@@  4...e6  5.Bb2  Nc6  6.d4  cxd4  7.Nxd4  @@StartBracket@@see the variation@@EndBracket@@. }
5. Bb2 Nc6 6. d4 cxd4 7. Nxd4 Nf6 8. Nxc6 dxc6 9. e5 Nd5
{ If Black trades queens instead, we recapture with the rook and still plant our knight on e4. In that case, Black has less counterplay since the queens are gone. }
10. Ne4
{ The hole on d6 makes our life easy, with the knight on e4 always ready to land there. We just may need to eliminate the only obstacle on the way - the knight on d5 - after a3 @@StartBracket@@to prevent unwelcome Nb4 in case we push c4 too soon@@EndBracket@@ and then c4. Note that Black would have been totally fine if the pawn was on c7 instead of c6, as the d6 is protected. }
*

