1. Nf3 g6
{ We believe this move might be one of the worst responses to 1. Nf3. It may be played by somebody who likes developing the bishop to g7, King's Indian Defense fans, and whoever may like playing Pirc Defense or Modern Defense vs. 1. e4. }
2. e4
{ The only time in the course we suggest going e4 as early as on move  2. We may need to step outside of our comfort zone a bit and learn a few lines that may normally occur after @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@1.e4  c5  2.Nf3  g6  or  1.e4  g6  2.d4  Bg7  3.Nf3  . The effort will be well rewarded though as White has a sizeable advantage in all cases. }
2... c5
{ 2...Bg7  3.d4  d6   3...c5  4.dxc5  This line is covered in chapter 4.1.  4.Bc4!  The most active square for the bishop, from where it will be pressuring the f7.  4...Nf6  5.Qe2  Our goal is to short castle and finish the queenside development quickly. We may also occasionally employ a swift attack e4-e5 if Black allows it. }
3. d4 Bg7
{ 3...cxd4  4.Qxd4!  This leads to a Sicilian Dragon, where Black goes g6 as early as possible. We will suggest a few new ideas here in Chapter 4.1. }
4. dxc5 Qa5+ 5. c3 Qxc5 6. Na3
{ The goal is to play Be3 and Nb5. White enjoys a nice edge in all lines. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "4.1) 1...g6 2.e4 Bg7"]
[Black "3...c6 4.Bd3 d6 "]
[Result "*"]

1. Nf3 g6
{ We know quite a few people who play 1... g6 pretty much against anything. In our not-so-humble opinion, 2. e4 will wreck their defenses and inflict severe pain on the Black's king. Chapter 4.1 will cover 2...Bg7, which leads to Pirc/ Modern Defense type of positions, 4.2 and 4.3 will deal with 2... c5, which may lead to a rare line of Pirc or Accelerated Dragon variation of Sicilian Defense.  Arguably, 1... g6 is one of the worst moves out there against 1. Nf3. Black simply gives away too much space in the middle. }
2. e4
{ We must bite the bullet, take a deep breath, and go e4 as soon as on move 2! }
2... Bg7 3. d4 c6
{ Gives up a chunk of space and, therefore, can't be recommended. } 4. Bd3 d6
5. O-O Nf6 6. c3 { Securing the safety of our center. } 6... O-O 7. h3
{ Stops ...Bg4. Black is running out of space. Our plan is to play Re1 and then e5 or Nbd2-Nf1-Ng3, depending on the circumstances. }
