3. d4 Bg7 4. dxc5 Na6
{ Bizzare knight development, quite frankly. No wonder, White achieves a huge advantage in every single line. }
5. Bxa6 bxa6 { This is utterly ugly. } 6. Qd5 Rb8 7. Ne5
{ Hitting the f7 pawn and threatening to checkmate in 1. It's worth noting White needs to play fast and provoke as many weaknesses as possible before Black wakes up and finally catches up in development. }
