Nxe4 { 10...Bf8  11.Qd1  Bxc5  12.Nd3+- } 11. Nxe4 Rxe4 12. Nc6
{ That's the one! A truly satisfying tactic, which indirectly hits the rook on e4! }
12... Qf6
{ 12...dxc6  13.Qxc6+  Bd7  14.Qxe4+-  With so much extra material and Black's damaged pawn structure, White's win is only a matter of time. }
13. Nxa7
{ White wins quite easily after Bb7 on the next move - Qb8 and picks up a bishop on b7. If Black defends better and goes Qd8 - we can simply take on c8 and follow up with Bg5. In both cases, Black's defenses will crumble soon enough. }
