Qxc5 6. Na3
{ The knight on the rim is not always dim. Here, we are aiming for Be3 and Nb5. }
6... Nf6 7. Nb5
{ An impressive pawn sacrifice. We need to attack while Black is still behind in development. }
7... Nxe4
{ The most tempting move, which needs to be checked and memorized before anything else. }
8. Be3 Qc6 9. Nfd4
{ Hitting the queen but the ultimate prize we are after is the bishop on g7. }
9... Bxd4 10. cxd4
{ In addition to a bishop pair and better development, White also has a deadly threat of Rc1 and Nc7. }
10... O-O 11. d5 { The queen is running out of space } 11... Qf6 12. Qc2
{ Before trapping the rook with the knight, we need to hit the Black's knight and protect the pawn on b2. }
12... Nd6 13. Nc7
{ White wins the rook and, on top of that, should be able to come back safely from a8 to c7. With such a huge material advantage, winning should not be a real challenge @@StartBracket@@just don't blunder anything huge!@@EndBracket@@. }
