8. Be3 Qc6 9. Na7
{ A nice double attack from a highly unsual position for a knight. } 9... Qc7
10. Nxc8 Qxc8 11. Nd2 Nf6 12. g3
{ A slightly unusual fiancetto. We believe the bishop on g2 is in a better position to support our kingside expansion as opposed to e2 or d3. }
12... O-O 13. Bg2 Ng4
{ Looks tempting for Black but doesn't accomplish much as we don't plan to give up our dark-squared bishop. }
14. Bg5 Re8 15. h3 { Kicking the annoying knight out. } 15... Ne5 16. O-O
{ White's plan is to push the pawns on the kingside and attack Black's king. }
