4... Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Qa4 d5
{ Hardly makes any sense since we can immediately attack Black on the a4-e8 diagonal with Bb5. }
7. Bb5 dxe4 8. Ne5 Bd7 9. Bxc6
{ 9.Nxc6?  bxc6  10.Bxc6  Rc8  11.Bxd7+  Qxd7  12.Qxd7  Nxd7  13.Be3  Looks like White inevitably wins one of the Black pawns. However, it comes at a price.  13...f5!  14.Bxa7  Bg7=  Black's activity is sufficient for full compensation. }
9... bxc6 10. Qc4 e6 11. Bg5 Be7 12. O-O-O
{ A beautiful development and attack on the open file at the same time. } 12...
Nd5 13. Bxe7 Qxe7 14. Nxe4 { The threat of Qc5, followed by c4, is decisive. }
