{ Steinitz, the first world champ, once said that whoever has the initiative must attack; otherwise, the initiative would evaporate. We fully agree. }
9... Qc5 10. Ne4 Qb6 11. h3 { The only way! } 11... Qxb2 12. Bb5
{ An astounding double rook sacrifice, reminiscent of the evergreen classical game of 1800s, Anderssen-Kizeritsky. }
12... Qxa1+ { 12...Bd7  13.O-O!+-  Nc5  is coming, among many other threats. }
13. Ke2 Qxh1 14. Bxc6+ Bd7
{ 14...bxc6  allows mate in 3.  15.Qxc6+  Bd7  16.Qxa8+  Bc8  17.Qxc8# } 15.
Bxd7+ Kd8 16. Be8
{ Black can only procrastinate the checkmate on d7 for so long. } *

