4... Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Qa4 d6 7. e5
{ This break in the center improves our knight and damages Black's pawn structure. }
7... Nd7
{ Almost loses as will be seen in the subsequent lines. The main reason: we take on d6 right away, ruining Black's structure if they retake with the e7-pawn @@StartBracket@@since the newly created pawn on d6 after the recapture is an isolated pawn with no chances for survival after the trivial Bf4 and O-O-O@@EndBracket@@. Black doesn't have enough time to attack us @@StartBracket@@like Nc5 or Nb6@@EndBracket@@ and take on d6 with the queen either since it may run into a quick Nb5 and Bf4 @@StartBracket@@and then Nc7@@EndBracket@@. It will certainly become crystal clear once you examine the upcoming lines carefully. }
