8... Qh5 9. Nc3 c6 10. Qc2
{ Forcing Black to play d5 and weaken the dark squares. } 10... d5 11. e3
{ As usual, preparing Ne2 and Nf4. } 11... Nbd7 12. Ne2 g5
{ Otherwise, we go Nf4. } 13. Ne5 Bd6 14. f3
{ Black's attack on the kingside was quite short-lived. We should bring the rooks together @@StartBracket@@Rae1@@EndBracket@@ and prepare for e4, exposing Black's king. }
