{ An impatient move, trying to fianchetto the bishop before having any grip on the center. }
8. d5
{ Now ...Bb7 is not happening since we have c4 and Ng5, hitting e6 hard. } 8...
e5 9. dxe6 Bxe6 { Loses rather quickly. } 10. Ng5
{ Now Black can't keep up with our threats. } 10... Bf7 11. Nxf7 Rxf7 12. Bc4
d5 13. Bxf6 { A crucial move, winning a pawn. } 13... Bxf6 14. Bxd5
{ At the very least, White is winning an exchange and then saves the rook on a1 with c3. From there, our plan would be Qc2-Nd2-Rad1; the ideal scenario is to trade as much as you can and get a winning endgame. }
