1. Nf3
{ In our final chapter, we are going to face the least challenging first move. We have covered a lot of ground, so let's finish with a line that is pleasant, enjoyable and something we can certainly beat! }
1... b5
{ One of least challenging moves. No wonder that this chapter is going to be the shortest. Our path to advantage is crystal clear. }
2. e4 a6
{ May work in a bullet game, but for sure isn't a suitable weapon for long time control. }
3. d4 Bb7 4. Bd3
{ This move is the simplest. The point is to keep the knight on b1 for a while and eventually bring it into the game via d2 and then f1 to g3. }
4... e6 5. O-O c5 6. c3
{ The cornerstone of our strategy. The pawn solidifies our center. } 6... Nf6
7. Re1 { The plan: Nbd2-f1-g3, then e5 and attack! } *

